; M3 gate: sticky state (GATE / VEL) is re-established at a loop point. The
; linear MMB encoder omits a PARAM_SET whose value already matches the state at
; the #loop marker, but the loop TAIL leaves a different sticky state that would
; otherwise bleed into the loop body on iterations 2+ — playing the full-gate
; head notes short (gh002/ACTRAISER fm1 `:gate- 0t`). The exporter restores the
; marker's snapshot (gate/vel/active macros) before JUMP, so every iteration
; replays identically. Both gate and vel drift here, on FM and PSG.
(fm1 :tempo 200 :alg 4 :fb 3 :ar1 31 :tl1 20 :ar4 31 :tl4 8 :len 8
  #loop c e g
  :gate* 0.5 :vel 8 c e g
  (go loop))
(sqr1 :len 8
  #loop c e g
  :gate* 0.5 :vel 6 c e g
  (go loop))
